resources.string: Intro to CBT: Why Thoughts Matter
Mental Hub is here to guide you through the application. If you are having a hard time navigating the application click the tutorial image.
This can be journal content that can be long
How are you? Write everything that happened to you here today.
I am terrified of being overweight
Avoid eating when I am hungry
Have gone on eating binges where I felt that I may not be able to stop
Cut my food into small pieces
Aware of the calorie content of foods that I eat
Particularly avoid food with a high carbohydrates content (i.e. bread, rice, potatoes, etc.)
Feel that others would prefer if I ate more
Am preoccupied with a desire to be thinner
Think about burning calories when I exercise
Other people think that I am too thin
Am preoccupied with the thought of having fat on my body
Take longer than others to eat my meals
Avoid foods with sugar in them
Feel that food controls my life
Feel that others pressure me to eat
Give too much time and thought about food
Like my stomach to be empty
Have the impulse to vomit after meals
